cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about improving the performance of neural end-to-end text-to-speech models, which falls under the domain of natural language processing.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech synthesis and improving the voice quality of TTS systems.
- cs.SI (Speech and Audio Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of TTS models by introducing a distillation loss function.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes a teacher-student training scheme for Tacotron-based TTS, which involves knowledge distillation.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with improving the performance of TTS systems, which can be seen as a control problem.
